<storybody><![CDATA[<p>Minutes after External Affairs Minister Sushma Swaraj asking people to greet Africans by shaking hands and saying 'India loves you', Twitter exploded with jokes, memes and even racist taunts at the idea.</p><p>While Swaraj had tweeted the idea in light of the recent attacks on citizens of various African countries in India, many netizens seemed more inclined to mock the suggestion.</p><p>Of course, the plan found some backers too. The minister retweeted one user who claimed to have greeted an African and left him with a smile.</p><p>A number of tweets just took the opportunity to let loose some jokes but disconcertingly, some handles unleashed more racist tweets, even stereotyping people on their skin colours.</p><p>The majority of tweets however, were just harmless jokes with many tagging their favourite South African cricketers and telling them India loves you.</p><p><b>&nbsp;Here are some of the tweets:</b></p>  <blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">I appeal to fellow Indians. Next time you meet an African citizen, pl shake hand and say 'India loves you'.<br />Pl RT</p>&amp;; Sushma Swaraj (@SushmaSwaraj) <a href="https://twitter.com/SushmaSwaraj/status/738228679289896961" mce_href="https://twitter.com/SushmaSwaraj/status/738228679289896961">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script> <p>&nbsp; <br /></p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Next time you receive an email from a Nigerian Prince, immediately reply 'India loves you'</p>&amp;; Sidvee (@sidvee) <a href="https://twitter.com/sidvee/status/738238996266913792" mce_href="https://twitter.com/sidvee/status/738238996266913792">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script> <blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en"><a href="https://twitter.com/SushmaSwaraj" mce_href="https://twitter.com/SushmaSwaraj">@SushmaSwaraj</a> I did this today :) And the man from Senegal had the broadest smile money can't buy. <a href="https://t.co/HMweMPRMcp" mce_href="https://t.co/HMweMPRMcp">https://t.co/HMweMPRMcp</a></p>&amp;; Ajay (@unitechvictim) <a href="https://twitter.com/unitechvictim/status/738319201228578816" mce_href="https://twitter.com/unitechvictim/status/738319201228578816">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Say India loves you before asking them maal hai kya.</p>&amp;; frootifer vajpayee (@Oinkoo) <a href="https://twitter.com/Oinkoo/status/738336219453526016" mce_href="https://twitter.com/Oinkoo/status/738336219453526016">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">I appeal to fellow Indians. Next time you meet a TMC Supporter, Please Shake Hand and say "India Loves You". <br />Please RT.</p>&amp;; TheFrustratedIndian (@FrustIndian) <a href="https://twitter.com/FrustIndian/status/738315664654356480" mce_href="https://twitter.com/FrustIndian/status/738315664654356480">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script> <blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">She: tell me those 3 magical words<br />"INDIA LOVES YOU"</p>&amp;; Sanjay (@oothikicha) <a href="https://twitter.com/oothikicha/status/738286670164828160" mce_href="https://twitter.com/oothikicha/status/738286670164828160">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script> <blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Aren't we supposed to fold our hands &amp; say namaste?  What's all this handshaking &amp; India loves you business? Where's the culture police?</p>&amp;; Moon (@moonsez) <a href="https://twitter.com/moonsez/status/738264125034233856" mce_href="https://twitter.com/moonsez/status/738264125034233856">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">India Loves You*.</p><p>*Conditions apply.</p>&amp;; Krupakar Manukonda (@krupakar_m) <a href="https://twitter.com/krupakar_m/status/738249063213236224" mce_href="https://twitter.com/krupakar_m/status/738249063213236224">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Yo <a href="https://twitter.com/ABdeVilliers17" mce_href="https://twitter.com/ABdeVilliers17">@ABdeVilliers17</a>, India loves you. <a href="https://t.co/4H0umUNBQ3" mce_href="https://t.co/4H0umUNBQ3">https://t.co/4H0umUNBQ3</a></p>&amp;; Nigel Britto (@NigelBritto) <a href="https://twitter.com/NigelBritto/status/738244459180269568" mce_href="https://twitter.com/NigelBritto/status/738244459180269568">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Indians: India loves you<br />Africans: <a href="https://t.co/dRHzo7fHWk" mce_href="https://t.co/dRHzo7fHWk">pic.twitter.com/dRHzo7fHWk</a></p>&amp;; Amit (@Goddamittt) <a href="https://twitter.com/Goddamittt/status/738240709086613504" mce_href="https://twitter.com/Goddamittt/status/738240709086613504">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Dear Jonty Rhodes, India loves you</p>&amp;; Ajith (@ajith27) <a href="https://twitter.com/ajith27/status/738239740588085249" mce_href="https://twitter.com/ajith27/status/738239740588085249">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="tl">Indian: India loves you.<br />African: I too love India.<br />Jhonty Rhodes: Toh main yeh rishta pakka samzoon?</p>&amp;; ???? (@FaaduTweets) <a href="https://twitter.com/FaaduTweets/status/738338725826961409" mce_href="https://twitter.com/FaaduTweets/status/738338725826961409">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">Not making jokes about African People is very hard to racist.</p>&amp;; Manish (@Slysterr) <a href="https://twitter.com/Slysterr/status/738326850133360640" mce_href="https://twitter.com/Slysterr/status/738326850133360640">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en">I appeal to fellow Indians. Next time you meet a Bihari, pl shake hand and say 'Raj Thackeray loves you'.<br />Pl RT</p>&amp;; Chandler Bing (@Being_Chandler) <a href="https://twitter.com/Being_Chandler/status/738295736572497920" mce_href="https://twitter.com/Being_Chandler/status/738295736572497920">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script> <blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><p dir="ltr" lang="en"><a href="https://twitter.com/Alllahdin" mce_href="https://twitter.com/Alllahdin">@Alllahdin</a> so realistic..</p></blockquote><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en">&amp;; zorba (@khannaa) <a href="https://twitter.com/khannaa/status/738342959842631681" mce_href="https://twitter.com/khannaa/status/738342959842631681">June 2, 2016</a></blockquote><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-lang="en"><br /></blockquote><b>
<script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
ALSO READ:</b><br /><b><a href="http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sushhma-swaraj-attack-on-africans-in-delhi/1/683180.html ">Shake hand and say India loves you: Sushma Swaraj's appeal to Indians when they meet Africans</a></b> <p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p></blockquote> <script async="" src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" mce_src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script><p>&nbsp;</p>]]></storybody>
